package logic

    Description
    Branch
    Enumeration representing different branches with their associated values.
    BranchReports
    This class represents the reports associated with a specific branch, including income, quarterly, performance, and order reports.
    Category
    Enumeration representing the different categories of items available.
    CertifiedWorker
    The CertifiedWorker class extends the User class and represents a worker certified to work at a specific restaurant.
    ClientInfo
    The ClientInfo class represents the information of a client, including their name, address, and status.
    ConcreteItem
    ConcreteItem represents a specific item available in the restaurant menu.
    Doneness
    Enumeration representing the doneness level for a main meal item.
    Drinks
    Drinks represents a drink item in the restaurant menu.
    IncomeReport
    IncomeReport represents the income report for a specific restaurant.
    Item
    Abstract class representing an item in the restaurant menu.
    MainMeal
    MainMeal represents a main meal item in the restaurant menu.
    Menu
    The Menu class represents a menu with a unique identifier.
    MenuItem
    The MenuItem class represents the items in a menu.
    Message
    The Message class represents a message sent between the client and server.
    MessageType
    The MessageType enum represents the different types of messages that can be sent between the client and server.
    Order
    The Order class represents a customer's order in the restaurant system.
    OrderItem
    The OrderItem class represents the items within an order.
    OrderItemDetail
    The OrderItemDetail class represents the details of an item within an order.
    OrderReport
    The OrderReport class represents a report summarizing the orders in a restaurant for a given period.
    PerformanceReport
    The PerformanceReport class represents a report summarizing the performance of a restaurant in terms of order delivery times.
    PickUpType
    The PickUpType enum represents the types of order pickups available.
    Quarter
    The Quarter enum represents the four fiscal quarters of a year.
    QuarterReport
    The QuarterReport class represents a report summarizing the daily orders and revenue of a restaurant for a given quarter.
    Report
    The Report class serves as an abstract base class for various types of reports.
    ReportType
    The ReportType enum represents the types of reports that can be generated.
    Resturant
    The Resturant class represents a restaurant with its associated information.
    Salad
    The Salad class represents a salad item in the menu, with its associated ingredients and size.
    Size
    The Size enum represents the available sizes for items, such as Large, Medium, and Small.
    Sweets
    The Sweets class represents a sweet item in the menu, with its associated ingredients.
    User
    The User class represents a user in the system, with attributes such as name, ID, contact details, and account information.
    UserType
    The UserType enum represents different types of users in the system.
